Key Match Events: Pakistan chased down 107 to win by three wickets with seven balls to spare.
Pakistan slipped from 52-2 to 62-6 and then to 95-7 before securing the win.
Ireland slumped to 32-6 but managed to post 106-9 with Delany scoring 31 off 19 balls.
Imad took 3-8 and Afridi took 3-22 for Pakistan.
Shaheen Afridi hit a six to win the game for Pakistan.
Post-Match Reflections: Pakistan captain Babar Azam acknowledged the team's bowling strength but noted batting mistakes in previous matches against the USA and India.
Babar Azam emphasized the need to review and improve team performance.
Ireland captain Paul Stirling expressed pride in the team's fight despite not starting well and facing pressure from Pakistan.
Paul Stirling highlighted the need for better balance and tempo in T20 cricket.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Both Pakistan and Ireland had already been eliminated from Super 8s contention.
Andrew Leonard, an Irish cricket commentator, mentioned that Ireland's performance was not indicative of the team's current potential under Paul Stirling.
Daniel Norcross, a BBC commentator, referred to the group as a 'group of death' and noted Ireland's tough journey.
